This paper deals with algorithms for carrier and rate allocation in cellular systems, which are typically studied in the fields of networking and information theory. The use of CSMA-based algorithms also suggests a focus on network protocols and medium access control. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of heterogeneous networks and multi-carrier systems suggests a focus on multimedia applications, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with distributed algorithms, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
